pve-storage-zfsiscsimp (0.4.1) stable; urgency=medium

  * Publish the immutable artifact certified after the 0.4.0 laboratory rollout.
  * Use 5s/5s NOP-Out and converge existing sessions without disruptive logout.
  * Reject a failover run if the nominally healthy path becomes unusable.

 -- Joaquin Varela <joaquinv898@gmail.com>  Tue, 14 Jul 2026 16:55:00 -0300

pve-storage-zfsiscsimp (0.4.0) stable; urgency=medium

  * Bound all local iSCSI and multipath dataplane commands with timeouts.
  * Cap stale identity fallback at 120s and prohibit stale-WWID path remediation.
  * Re-resolve identity after a map-appearance failure (rollback/realloc race).
  * Consolidate the run_command and retry-loop idioms into two helpers; drop the
    SSH probe from saveconfig reads (their own ssh already bounds failover) while
    keeping the control-plane probe that bounds zfs_request failover.
  * Fix file_set_contents force_utf8 misuse that corrupted non-ASCII CHAP secrets.
  * Require at least one live iSCSI session while tolerating degraded paths.
  * Add a bounded login_timeout and keep the 5s NOP-Out/replacement settings.
  * Drop LIO-irrelevant options (comstar_*, nowritecache) and other dead code.

 -- Joaquin Varela <joaquinv898@gmail.com>  Tue, 14 Jul 2026 16:30:00 -0300

